docs.abstract: It is a small but significant concession to the United States and Israel, which want U.N. peacekeepers to more aggressively pursue Hezbollah activity near the Israeli border.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The authority of peacekeeping forces in southern Lebanon is a matter of annual debate at the United Nations, pitting security concerns against sovereignty rights. But for the first time in recent memory, the Security Council this year will formally review the size of the forces and allow cuts to be considered when it  renews the mission, three officials said on Wednesday.

headline.main: U.N. Vote Could Clear Path to Cutting Peacekeepers in Southern Lebanon
headline.print_headline: U.N. to Study Smaller Force To Keep Peace In Lebanon

docs.abstract: The announcement by Joe Manchin III, a rare moderate Democrat in the Senate, brought relief to party leaders who feared losing his seat to Republicans if he stepped down.
docs.snippet: The announcement by Joe Manchin III, a rare moderate Democrat in the Senate, brought relief to party leaders who feared losing his seat to Republicans if he stepped down.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Joe Manchin III announced on Tuesday that he would not run for governor in his home state of West Virginia, ending speculation about the future of one of the Senate’s few moderate Democrats — and bringing relief to party leaders who feared Republicans would win his seat if he stepped down.

headline.main: Manchin Won’t Run for West Virginia Governor; Will Stay in Senate
headline.print_headline: Manchin Won’t Run for Governor, Choosing to Remain in the Senate

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump intervened Tuesday once again on behalf of a Navy SEAL who was charged but acquitted of war crimes in the death of a captured Islamic State fighter in Iraq, ordering the military to punish the prosecutors who tried the case in the first place.

headline.main: Trump Orders Navy to Strip Medals From Prosecutors in War Crimes Trial
